<p><strong>SCO Everseen Training – LMS Module</strong></p><p>To help reduce shrinkage in our stores, a software technology called Everseen has been installed into the Self-Service Checkout (SCO) machines. This helps SCO operators detect instances when items have not been scanned correctly.</p><p>This module takes you through how the Everseen technology operates and how SCO operators can use the technology to assist customers and reduce shrink in stores.</p><p><strong>Audience:</strong> SCO team members and all managers in our stores</p><p><strong>Duration: </strong>10 minutes</p><p><strong>Audio: </strong>Yes, there are videos, please grab your headphones</p><p>If you wish to have the text in the module read out, follow the instructions <a href="https://kmartaus.sharepoint.com/sites/M365LP/OurLearningHubHelp/SitePages/Yourtraining.aspx" target="_blank">here(opens in a new tab)</a>.</p><p>Click <strong>START COURSE</strong> or select the first topic to begin.</p><p>Last updated: October 2024</p><p><em>Section 1 of 6</em></p><p><strong>What is Everseen and how does it work?</strong></p><p>Everseen technology is a software program installed on our SCO machines.</p><p>It detects when a customer has not scanned a product correctly including:<br /></p><ol><li>No scans - when a product is not scanned</li><li>Product switch - when the barcode of a cheaper item is scanned instead of a more expensive product</li><li>Basket base loss - when some products are scanned, and others are left in the basket and taken without payment</li></ol><p><strong>How does the technology work?<br /></strong></p><p><strong>(1) No scans<br /></strong>Move through the slides to find out.</p><ol><li>If a customer misses scanning an item that is placed into the bagging area, an intervention is triggered that requires team member assistance.</li></ol><p><img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," /></p><ol><li>The screen will show a missed scan has occurred as well as video footage of the event.</li></ol><p><img alt="A machine with a screen on it

AI-generated content may be incorrect." src="data:image/jpeg;base64," /></p><p>If a customer sees a video footage and has a question regarding privacy, contact your manager. You can also advise Kmart's privacy policy is on our website. Inquiries or complaints can be submitted in writing to <a href="mailto:kmartprivacyofficer@Kmart.com.au" target="_blank">kmartprivacyofficer@Kmart.com.au</a></p><p><strong>(2) Product switch</strong></p><p>Move through the slides to find out.</p><ol><li>When the barcode of a cheaper item is scanned instead of a more expensive product, an intervention is triggered that requires team member assistance.</li></ol><p><img alt="A cash register with a screen and a credit card reader

AI-generated content may be incorrect." src="data:image/jpeg;base64," /></p><ol><li>The screen will show messaging that this is a product switch with video footage of the event.</li></ol><p><img alt="A cash register with a screen and a payment terminal

AI-generated content may be incorrect." src="data:image/jpeg;base64," /></p><p><strong>(3) Basket base loss</strong></p><p>Move through the slides to find out.</p><ol><li>When some products are scanned, and others are left in the basket and taken without payment, an intervention is triggered that requires team member assistance.</li></ol><p><img alt="A cash register with a screen and a credit card reader

AI-generated content may be incorrect." src="data:image/jpeg;base64," /></p><ol><li>The screen will show messaging that this is a basket base loss with video footage of the event.</li></ol><p><img alt="A cash register with a screen and a payment terminal

AI-generated content may be incorrect." src="data:image/jpeg;base64," /></p><p><em>Section 2 of 6</em></p><p><strong>No scans/Basket base loss</strong></p><p>Whether it's a no scan or a basket base loss, the scanning of a product is being missed.</p><p><strong>Play the video</strong> to see what happens when a customer missed scanning a product.</p><p><strong>Key takeaway points</strong></p><ul><li>An intervention will occur the moment a non scanned product is detected.</li><li>This requires a team member to assist to review and ensure all items have been scanned.</li><li>If a scan is missed, the team member should assist the customer to ensure it is scanned.</li><li>This will occur every time a no scan occurs.</li></ul><p><strong>Check your knowledge</strong></p><p>What happens when a customer misses scanning a product at a SCO? </p><p>Choose your correct response.</p><ul><li>An intervention is triggered and requires a team member to assist <em>(Correctly selected)</em></li><li>The customer is given a 'nudge' to rescan the product <em>(Correctly unselected)</em></li><li>An alarm sounds to alert the store team members a product has not been scanned at a SCO <em>(Correctly unselected)</em></li></ul><p><strong>Correct</strong></p><p>That's right. If a customer misses scanning an item that is placed into the bagging area, an intervention is triggered and requires a team member to assist.</p><p><em>Section 3 of 6</em></p><p><strong>Product switch</strong></p><p>Select the video below to learn more about product switch.</p><p><strong>Check your knowledge</strong></p><p>True or false? A product that has had its barcode switched will prompt the customer to scan the product again.</p><ul><li>True <em>(Correctly unselected)</em></li><li>False <em>(Correctly selected)</em></li></ul><p><strong>Correct</strong></p><p>That's right. A product that has had its barcode switched will trigger an intervention and require a team member to respond and assist the customer to clear the intervention.</p><p>Now that you know about the types of interventions, let’s learn how to approach our customers when an intervention has occurred.</p><p><em>Section 4 of 6</em></p><p><strong>What do you say to customers when an intervention has occurred?</strong></p><p>It's important to note that every customer is provided with great customer service and is never accused of any wrongdoing. Missed scans can be accidental and each case should be treated the same.</p><p><strong>Scenario 1:</strong></p><p><strong>A customer misses scanning a product. What do you say?</strong></p><p>A customer is at a SCO and scans some products correctly and places them into the bagging area. They missed scanning a product. The SCO triggers an intervention showing video footage of the item not scanned.</p><p><strong>Press play</strong> to find out what to say to our customers when this intervention has occurred.</p><p><strong>Scenario 2:</strong></p><p><strong>A customer scans a different product barcode to the product placed into the bagging area. What do you say?</strong></p><p><strong>Press play</strong> to find out.</p><p><strong>If multiple product switches occur in one transaction, notify your manager to assist.</strong></p><p><br /><strong>Check your knowledge</strong></p><p>As a team member, what steps must you take when a SCO triggers a "Product Barcode Switch" intervention for a customer?</p><p>Select the correct option.</p><ul><li>Let the customer rescan the correct item and continue. <em>(Correctly unselected)</em></li><li>Remove the incorrect item by scanning your operator code, review what has been scanned, select "Rescan item," and scan the correct product.</li><li>Correctly selected</li><li>Cancel the transaction and ask the customer to start again.</li><li>Correctly unselected</li><li>Nothing as the transaction will proceed without any issues.</li><li>Correctly unselected</li></ul><p><strong>Correct</strong></p><p>That's right. In this situation, remove the incorrect item by scanning your operator code, review what has been scanned, select "Rescan item," and scan the correct product.</p><p><strong>If an intervention occurs, and you’re faced with a threatening situation from a customer, always remember to follow the 4D's and notify the manager on duty immediately.</strong></p><p><strong>For helpful tips on SCO Everseen technology, refer to the guide below.</strong></p><p><em>Section 5 of 6</em></p><p><strong>Quiz</strong></p><p>We're almost at the end of the module! Take this short quiz to see what you've learnt in this module. You need to answer 4 out of 5 questions correctly or achieve 80% to pass.</p><p><strong><em>Question</em></strong></p><p><strong>01/05</strong></p><p>A customer is shown a video of their intervention. They express concerns about their privacy and want to speak to someone about it. What do you do? Select all that apply.</p><ul><li>Refer them to a manager <em>(Correctly checked)</em></li><li>Tell them about Kmart’s Privacy Policy on the Kmart website <em>(Correctly checked)</em></li><li>Tell them that all stores have this technology. It’s been around for a while</li></ul><p><em>(Correctly unchecked)</em></p><ul><li>Tell them they can make their inquiry or complaint to Kmart’s Privacy Officer <em>(Correctly checked)</em></li></ul><p><strong>Correct</strong></p><p>That's right. Do not brush aside a customer’s concern about their privacy. Always refer them to a manager and Kmart’s Privacy Policy on the Kmart website where they can make an inquiry or lodge a formal complaint to Kmart’s Privacy Officer.</p><p><strong><em>Question</em></strong></p><p><strong>02/05</strong></p><p>True or false? A customer missed scanning a product, you approach them and say: "Looks like the product didn't scan through. Let me scan that for you.”</p><ul><li>True <em>(Correctly unselected)</em></li><li>False <em>(Correctly selected)</em></li></ul><p><strong>Correct</strong></p><p>That's right. Always be polite and greet the customer first before clearing the intervention, for example start the conversation with: "Hi how are you today?" then say "Looks like the product didn't scan through. Let me scan that for you.”</p><p><strong><em>Question</em></strong></p><p><strong>03/05</strong></p><p>A customer missed scanning a product. An intervention is triggered and a team member assists. Once the customer scans the product, they can continue with their transaction.</p><ul><li>True <em>(Correctly selected)</em></li><li>False <em>(Correctly unselected)</em></li></ul><p><strong>Correct</strong></p><p>That's right. The system will trigger an intervention so a team member can assist to ensure all products are scanned into the transaction correctly.</p><p><strong><em>Question</em></strong></p><p><strong>04/05</strong></p><p>True or false? If a customer scanned a product barcode that belongs to another product, question them first, then attempt to clear the intervention for them.</p><ul><li>True (Correctly unselected)</li><li>False (Correctly selected)</li></ul><p><strong>Correct</strong></p><p>That's right. Never question a customer. Simply say: "Hi how are you today? It looks like that product has scanned under a different code. I'll clear this for you, so the correct product displays.”</p><p><strong><em>Question</em></strong></p><p><strong>05/05</strong></p><p>A customer has scanned an item using a different barcode that triggers a product switch intervention. What happens now? Select all that apply.</p><ul><li>The team member reviews the footage to identify the product switch. <em>(Correctly checked)</em></li><li>The team member checks that all items have been scanned correctly.</li></ul><p><em>(Correctly checked)</em></p><ul><li>The product switch item is removed from the transaction. <em>(Correctly checked)</em></li><li>Advise a manager if a customer performs multiple product switches in one transaction. <em>(Correctly checked)</em></li></ul><p><strong>Correct</strong></p><p>That's right. It’s important to notify a manager of customers who trigger multiple product switches in one transaction so they can assist with service and also report the incident into Auror with the Profit Protection Business Partner.</p><p><em>Section 6 of 6</em></p><p><strong>Summary</strong></p><p><strong>Congratulations.
